%h3 Privacy Policy
%p.lead
  Your privacy is very important to us. Accordingly, we have developed this Policy in order for you to know
  and understand how we collect, use, communicate, disclose, and apply your personal information. The
  following outlines our privacy policy.

  %ul
    %li
      Before or at the time of collecting personal information, we will identify the purposes for which
      information is being collected.

    %li
      We will collect and use of personal information solely with the objective of fulfilling those purposes
      specified by us and for other compatible purposes, unless we obtain the consent of the individual
      concerned or as required by law.

    %li
      We will only retain personal information as long as necessary for the fulfillment of those purposes.

    %li
      We will collect personal information by lawful and fair means and, where appropriate, with the
      knowledge or consent of the individual concerned.

    %li
      Personal data should be relevant to the purposes for which it is to be used, and, to the extent
      necessary for those purposes, should be accurate, complete, and up-to-date.

    %li
      We will protect personal information by reasonable security safeguards against loss or theft, as
      well as unauthorized access, disclosure, copying, use or modification.

    %li
      We will make readily available to customers information about our policies and practices relating
      to the management of personal information.

%p
  We are committed to conducting our business in accordance with these principles in order to ensure that
  the confidentiality of personal information is protected and maintained. This Privacy Policy is incorporated
  by reference into the SnazzDat’s Terms of Service. The term "We," "Us," "Our," or "SnazzDat" includes
  SnazzDat Inc., our affiliates, and SnazzDat.com. It explains how we may: collect, use and disclose
  the information we obtain through the SnazzDat Service. The "SnazzDat Service" is defined as
  SnazzDat.com and the associated mobile applications and Internet service under our control, whether
  partial or otherwise, in connection with providing a platform for SnazzDat services.

%strong Scope
%p
  This Privacy Policy covers how we treat personal information ("Personal Information") and other
  information that we obtain through the SnazzDat Service.

%p
  What information do we collect?
  %br/
  SnazzDat collects information from you when you register on our site, respond to a survey, fill out a form
  or make an appointment with any of our Partners. When you register on our site, as appropriate, you will
  be asked to provide your Name, Mailing Address, E-mail address, Phone Number, Body Measurements,
  Favorite Colors, etc.


%strong Data Use.

%p
  Any of the information we collect from you may be used in one of the following ways:

%ol
  %li
    Personalize your experience- your information helps us better respond to your individual fashion
    needs.

  %li
    Enhance your experience on our website because we continually strive to improve our website
    offerings based on the information and feedback we receive from you.

  %li
    Improve customer service because your information helps us to more effectively respond to your
    customer service requests and support needs.

  %li
    To administer a contest, promotion, survey or other site feature from any of our Partners.

  %li
    To send periodic emails - the email address you provide, may be used to send you information and
    updates pertaining to your order or appointments, in addition to receiving occasional company news,
    updates, related product or service information, etc.

  %li
    Your information; whether public or private, will not be sold, exchanged, transferred, or given to any
    other company for any reason whatsoever, without your consent, other than for the express purpose of
    delivering the service requested.

  %li
